 contents: ["The federal government requires us to verify your household income every year to see if you’re still eligible for help paying for coverage. We do this by checking tax data from the Internal Revenue Service (IRS), but need your consent. If you do not give us permission to check IRS data, you can’t get help paying for coverage.", "If you want to continue to receive a tax credit to help pay your monthly premiums, or cost-sharing reductions that lower other health care costs in <coverage year>, call DC Health Link as soon as possible at (855) 532-5465. Tell customer service that you want to update your IRS consent."],
